-- Old Mutual Paid CEO 1.93 Million Pounds in 2011
-- B y   E d w a r d   E v a n s
-- 2012-03-29T13:49:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-29/old-mutual-paid-ceo-1-93-million-pounds-in-2011-correct-.html
(Corrects incentive payments, totals from first
paragraph.)  Old Mutual Plc (OML)  said it paid Chief
Executive Officer Julian Roberts 1.93 million pounds ($3
million) in total compensation for 2011.  He received 850,000 pounds in base salary, 297,500 pounds
in benefits, the company said in its annual report today. He
received 610,000 pounds as a cash bonus and a further 130,000
pounds from an earlier short-term incentive plan.  To contact the reporter on this story:
